transaction.charityRegisteredNumber.title                                           = What is the charity’s registered number?
transaction.charityRegisteredNumber.heading                                         = What is the charity’s registered number?
transaction.charityRegisteredNumber.checkYourAnswersLabel                           = Charity’s registered number
transaction.charityRegisteredNumber.hint                                            = Their charity number should be 5-8 digits long and may contain letters
transaction.charityRegisteredNumber.error.required                                  = Enter the charity’s registered number
transaction.charityRegisteredNumber.error.length                                    = The charity’s registered number must be 14 characters or fewer
transaction.charityRegisteredNumber.change.hidden                                   = Charity Registered Number
transaction.charityRegisteredNumber.regex                                           = The charity’s registered number must only include letters a to z, numbers 0 to 9, ampersands (&), apostrophes, at signs (@), forward slashes, full stops, hyphens, question marks and spaces
transaction.charityRegisteredNumber.missing                                         = Enter charity registered number

transaction.deferringPayment.title                                                  = Deferring payment
transaction.deferringPayment.heading                                                = Deferring payment
transaction.deferringPayment.p1                                                     = SDLT payment may be deferred when the whole or part of the chargeable consideration:
transaction.deferringPayment.li1                                                    = is uncertain or contingent on future events, like obtaining planning permission
transaction.deferringPayment.li2                                                    = becomes payable, or may become payable, more than six months after the effective date of transaction
transaction.deferringPayment.h2                                                     = Is the purchaser applying for a deferment?
transaction.deferringPayment.checkYourAnswersLabel                                  = Is the purchaser applying for a deferment?
transaction.deferringPayment.error.required                                         = Select yes if the purchaser is applying for a deferment
transaction.deferringPayment.change.hidden                                          = if the purchaser is applying for a deferment

transaction.transactionUseOfLandOrProperty.title                                    = The use of the land or property
transaction.transactionUseOfLandOrProperty.heading                                  = The use of the land or property
transaction.transactionUseOfLandOrProperty.subheading                               = What is the land or property to be used for?
transaction.transactionUseOfLandOrProperty.p1                                       = Non-residential property is defined by exclusion, which means any land or property that does not meet the specific definition of residential property.
transaction.transactionUseOfLandOrProperty.p2                                       = As a non-residential property, the classification for this return depends on the actual use, or suitability for use, on the effective date of the transaction.
transaction.transactionUseOfLandOrProperty.office                                   = Office
transaction.transactionUseOfLandOrProperty.hotel                                    = Hotel
transaction.transactionUseOfLandOrProperty.shop                                     = Shop
transaction.transactionUseOfLandOrProperty.warehouse                                = Warehouse
transaction.transactionUseOfLandOrProperty.factory                                  = Factory
transaction.transactionUseOfLandOrProperty.otherIndustrialUnit                      = Other industrial unit
transaction.transactionUseOfLandOrProperty.other                                    = Other
transaction.transactionUseOfLandOrProperty.error.required                           = Select at least one use for the land or property
transaction.transactionUseOfLandOrProperty.change.hidden                            = The use of the land or property
transaction.transactionUseOfLandOrProperty.hint                                     = Select all that apply
transaction.transactionUseOfLandOrProperty.checkYourAnswersLabel                    = How the land or property will be used
transaction.transactionUseOfLandOrProperty.missing                                  = Select how the land or property will be used

transaction.considerationsAffectedUncertain.title                                   = Considerations affected by uncertain future events - About the transaction
transaction.considerationsAffectedUncertain.heading                                 = Considerations affected by uncertain future events
transaction.considerationsAffectedUncertain.subHeading                              = Is any part of the consideration contingent or dependent on uncertain future events?
transaction.considerationsAffectedUncertain.error.required                          = Select yes if any part of the consideration is contingent or dependent on uncertain future events
transaction.considerationsAffectedUncertain.p1                                      = This means any SDLT payment that may be influenced by something yet to happen, like projected company profits or receiving planning permission.
transaction.considerationsAffectedUncertain.p2                                      = Uncertain future events are typically defined as:
transaction.considerationsAffectedUncertain.bullet1                                 = a contingent consideration, where a fixed sum is only paid, or not paid, when the uncertain future event occurs
transaction.considerationsAffectedUncertain.bullet2                                 = a dependent consideration, where the amount or value of a consideration depends on the uncertain future event

transaction.rulingFollowed.title                                                    = Have you followed the ruling under CAP1 or NSBC when completing this return?
transaction.rulingFollowed.heading                                                  = Have you followed the ruling under CAP1 or NSBC when completing this return?
transaction.rulingFollowed.yes                                                      = Yes
transaction.rulingFollowed.no                                                       = No
transaction.rulingFollowed.RulingNotReceived                                        = Ruling not yet received
transaction.rulingFollowed.checkYourAnswersLabel                                    = Have you followed the ruling under CAP1 or NSBC when completing this return?
transaction.rulingFollowed.hint                                                     = If you’ve received a ruling, confirm that you have followed that ruling when completing this return
transaction.rulingFollowed.error.required                                           = Select yes or no if you have received the ruling under CAP1 or NSBC, or select ‘Ruling not yet received’
transaction.rulingFollowed.change.hidden                                            = if you have followed the ruling under CAP1 or NSBC when completing this return

transaction.transactionSaleOfBusinessAssets.title                                   = What is included in the sale of the business?
transaction.transactionSaleOfBusinessAssets.heading                                 = What is included in the sale of the business?
transaction.transactionSaleOfBusinessAssets.hint                                    = Select all chargeable and non-chargeable assets that are included in this transaction
transaction.transactionSaleOfBusinessAssets.stock                                   = Stock
transaction.transactionSaleOfBusinessAssets.goodwill                                = Goodwill
transaction.transactionSaleOfBusinessAssets.chattelsAndMoveables                    = Chattels and moveables
transaction.transactionSaleOfBusinessAssets.others                                  = Others
transaction.transactionSaleOfBusinessAssets.checkYourAnswersLabel                   = What is included in the sale of the business?
transaction.transactionSaleOfBusinessAssets.error.required                          = Select at least one type of asset that is included in the sale of the business
transaction.transactionSaleOfBusinessAssets.change.hidden                           = What is included in the sale of the business?

transaction.saleOfBusiness.title                                                    = Sale of a business
transaction.saleOfBusiness.heading                                                  = Sale of a business
transaction.saleOfBusiness.subheading                                               = Is this transaction part of the sale of a business?
transaction.saleOfBusiness.paragraph                                                = If a transaction is part of the sale of a business, the land or property is separated from other assets that may not be liable for SDLT, like raw materials and machinery.
transaction.saleOfBusiness.checkYourAnswersLabel                                    = Is the transaction part of the sale of a business?
transaction.saleOfBusiness.error.required                                           = Select yes if this transaction is part of the sale of a business
transaction.saleOfBusiness.change.hidden                                            = Sale of a business

transaction.restrictionsCovenantsAndConditions.title                                = Restrictions, covenants and conditions
transaction.restrictionsCovenantsAndConditions.heading                              = Restrictions, covenants and conditions
transaction.restrictionsCovenantsAndConditions.h2                                   = Are there any restrictions, covenants or conditions affecting the value of the interest transferred or granted?
transaction.restrictionsCovenantsAndConditions.p1                                   = Restrictions, covenants, and conditions can affect the value of the interest transferred or granted by limiting how the land or property is used, altered, or developed.
transaction.restrictionsCovenantsAndConditions.li1                                  = Restrictions can define how the property is used or prohibit alterations, like extensions or conversions.
transaction.restrictionsCovenantsAndConditions.li2                                  = Covenants can dictate a property’s appearance, like exterior paint colours, types of fencing or the maintenance of a private road.
transaction.restrictionsCovenantsAndConditions.li3                                  = Conditions can afford the vendor certain rights, like the right to buy back the land or property at a reduced rate.
transaction.restrictionsCovenantsAndConditions.checkYourAnswersLabel                = Are there any restrictions, covenants or conditions affecting the value of the interest transferred or granted?
transaction.restrictionsCovenantsAndConditions.error.required                       = Select yes if there are restrictions, covenants or conditions affecting the value of the interest transferred or granted
transaction.restrictionsCovenantsAndConditions.change.hidden                        = if there are restrictions, covenants or conditions affecting the value of the interest transferred or granted

transaction.cap1OrNsbc.title                                                        = CAP1 or NSBC - About the transaction
transaction.cap1OrNsbc.heading                                                      = CAP1 or NSBC
transaction.cap1OrNsbc.subHeading                                                   = Have you applied for a CAP1 or NSBC in relation to this transaction?
transaction.cap1OrNsbc.p1                                                           = Clearance Applications Phase 1 (CAP1) and Non-Statutory Business Clearance (NSBC) service both provide formal written confirmation of HMRC’s view on how tax law applies to a specific transaction. They can help mitigate risk and provide clarity when there is uncertainty over tax obligations.
transaction.cap1OrNsbc.error.required                                               = Select yes if you have applied for a CAP1 or NSBC in relation to this transaction
transaction.cap1OrNsbc.checkYourAnswersLabel                                        = Have you applied for a CAP1 or NSBC in relation to the transaction?
transaction.cap1OrNsbc.change.hidden                                                = CAP1 or NSBC

transaction.isLandOrPropertyExchanged.title                                         = The exchange or part exchange of the land or property
transaction.isLandOrPropertyExchanged.heading                                       = The exchange or part exchange of the land or property
transaction.isLandOrPropertyExchanged.subheading                                    = Is any land or property being exchanged or part exchanged as part of this transaction?
transaction.isLandOrPropertyExchanged.paragraph                                     = Exchange or part exchange is when two parties are both receiving and releasing an area of land or property. This is treated as two separate transactions where each party is both a vendor and a purchaser.
transaction.isLandOrPropertyExchanged.checkYourAnswersLabel                         = Is any land or property being exchanged or part exchanged as part of this transaction?
transaction.isLandOrPropertyExchanged.error.required                                = Select yes if any land or property is being exchanged or part exchanged as part of this transaction
transaction.isLandOrPropertyExchanged.change.hidden                                 = Is any land or property being exchanged or part exchanged as part of this transaction?

transaction.totalAssetsConsideration.title                                          = Total consideration for all assets included in the sale of the business
transaction.totalAssetsConsideration.heading                                        = Total consideration for all assets included in the sale of the business
transaction.totalAssetsConsideration.checkYourAnswersLabel                          = The total consideration for the items included
transaction.totalAssetsConsideration.error.required                                 = Enter the total amount of consideration for the sale of the business, in pounds
transaction.totalAssetsConsideration.p1                                             = The total consideration must be apportioned on a just and reasonable basis, specifically for the land and items that are legally considered part of the land (fixtures).
transaction.totalAssetsConsideration.h2                                             = What is the total amount of consideration for the sale of the business apportioned to these items?
transaction.totalAssetsConsideration.hint                                           = Enter the value in whole pounds only, for example £200,000
transaction.totalAssetsConsideration.error.invalidNumeric                           = The total amount of consideration for the sale of the business must only include numbers 0 to 9 and commas
transaction.totalAssetsConsideration.error.invalidWholeNumber                       = Enter the total amount of consideration for the sale of the business in whole pounds
transaction.totalAssetsConsideration.error.maximum                                  = The total amount of consideration for the sale of the business must be equal to or less than £9,999,999,999
transaction.totalAssetsConsideration.change.hidden                                  = Total consideration for all assets included in the sale of the business

transaction.cisNumber.title                                                         = What is the purchaser’s CIS registration number?
transaction.cisNumber.heading                                                       = What is the purchaser’s CIS registration number?
transaction.cisNumber.hint                                                          = This is typically their 10-digit Unique Taxpayer Reference (UTR)
transaction.cisNumber.checkYourAnswersLabel                                         = What is the purchaser’s CIS registration number?
transaction.cisNumber.error.required                                                = Enter the purchaser’s CIS registration number
transaction.cisNumber.error.length                                                  = The purchaser’s CIS number must be 14 characters or less
transaction.cisNumber.invalid                                                       = invalid error
transaction.cisNumber.change.hidden                                                 = The purchaser’s CIS registration number

transaction.descriptionOfRestrictions.title                                         = What are the restrictions, covenants or conditions affecting the value of the interest transferred or granted? - About the transaction
transaction.descriptionOfRestrictions.heading                                       = What are the restrictions, covenants or conditions affecting the value of the interest transferred or granted?
transaction.descriptionOfRestrictions.subHeading                                    = Have you applied for a CAP1 or NSBC in relation to this transaction?
transaction.descriptionOfRestrictions.hint                                          = Provide a brief description, like a vendor`s right to buy back at less than market value
transaction.descriptionOfRestrictions.error.required                                = Enter a brief description of the restrictions, covenants or conditions affecting the value of the interest transferred or granted
transaction.descriptionOfRestrictions.error.regex                                   = The brief description of the restrictions, covenants or conditions must only include letters a to z, numbers 0 to 9, spaces and full stops
transaction.descriptionOfRestrictions.error.length                                  = The brief description of the restrictions, covenants or conditions must be 42 characters or fewer
transaction.descriptionOfRestrictions.checkYourAnswersLabel                         = What are the restrictions, covenants or conditions?
transaction.descriptionOfRestrictions.change.hidden                                 = Restrictions, covenants or conditions

transaction.transactionExercisingAnOption.title                                     = Exercising an option
transaction.transactionExercisingAnOption.heading                                   = Exercising an option
transaction.transactionExercisingAnOption.p                                         = This is when the transaction is the result of an option being exercised. The grant of an option and the subsequent purchase of the land or property are typically linked but considered two separate transactions.
transaction.transactionExercisingAnOption.subheading                                = Is this transaction pursuant to a previous option agreement?
transaction.transactionExercisingAnOption.checkYourAnswersLabel                     = Is this transaction pursuant to a previous option agreement?
transaction.transactionExercisingAnOption.error.required                            = Select yes if this transaction is pursuant to a previous option agreement
transaction.transactionExercisingAnOption.change.hidden                             = Is this transaction pursuant to a previous option agreement?

lease.beforeYouStart.p1                                                             = In this section, you need to tell us about the lease on the land or property.
lease.beforeYouStart.p2                                                             = We will ask for:
lease.beforeYouStart.l1.li1                                                         = the type of lease
lease.beforeYouStart.l1.li2                                                         = the lease start date
lease.beforeYouStart.l1.li3                                                         = the lease end date
lease.beforeYouStart.l1.li4                                                         = any rent-free period included in the lease
lease.beforeYouStart.l1.li5                                                         = the annual starting rent
lease.beforeYouStart.l1.li6                                                         = the end date for annual starting rent
lease.beforeYouStart.l1.li7                                                         = the later rent if known
lease.beforeYouStart.l1.li8                                                         = whether the later rent is more than £1,000
lease.beforeYouStart.l1.li9                                                         = the net present value (NPV)
lease.beforeYouStart.p3                                                             = You can also provide:
lease.beforeYouStart.l2.li1                                                         = the duration of the rent-free period
lease.beforeYouStart.l2.li2                                                         = the total amount of VAT on the annual rent
lease.beforeYouStart.l2.li3                                                         = the total premium payable including VAT

